<h2>Overview</h2><p>When it comes to adding personal touches to your Jeep, side steps can be a blend of functionality and style. In this article, we will explore the installation of the iArmor Aluminum Black Side Steps, installed by Angelo from MUDTRAIL, for a 2016 Jeep Wrangler Unlimited. Though designed for looks and convenience, it’s essential to understand what they can and cannot handle in terms of off-roading adventures.</p><h2>What This Covers</h2><p>This tutorial not only walks you through the installation process but also delves into the product's design, features, and real-world usability. While these side steps are aesthetically pleasing, they may not be as robust as traditional rocker sliders for hard-core off-roading.</p><h2>Step-by-Step Breakdown</h2><ol><li><strong>Remove Old Side Steps:</strong> Before installing the new side steps, the Jeep's OEM steps must be removed. You’ll need a 10mm and 13mm socket for this task. With six 10mm bolts and three 13mm bolts to pop off, this step is straightforward and quick.</li><li><strong>Unboxing the iArmor Steps:</strong> The steps arrive in a compact box and include all necessary hardware, including labeled mounting brackets and installation instructions. The product features a lightweight aluminum construction with a sleek black powder-coated finish.</li><li><strong>Installing the New Steps:</strong> Position the mounting brackets according to the installation guide. It’s advisable to have assistance since the side steps can be cumbersome. Use the provided washers and nuts for a secure fit.</li><li><strong>Adjust for Maximum Comfort:</strong> During the installation, check for any potential pinch points, such as where the steps might contact the Jeep's body. It may be necessary to add spacers to prevent the steps from scratching the paint or causing damage.</li><li><strong>Tightening and Final Adjustments:</strong> Once everything is lined up and secured, go through and tighten all bolts snugly. Afterward, test the stability of the steps before hitting the trails.</li></ol><h2>Helpful Tips</h2><ul><li>Always check the manufacturer's instructions for specific details on installation and compatibility.</li><li>Consider the weight capacity and overall design of the side steps; they are more decorative than functional for hardcore off-roading.</li><li>Having an extra set of hands can significantly simplify the installation process, particularly when holding up the side steps while securing the bolts.</li></ul><h2>Key Takeaways</h2><p>The iArmor Aluminum Black Side Steps are a stylish addition for everyday driving and light off-roading. While they gracefully replace OEM steps, buyers should be mindful of their intended use and limitations. For those seeking heavy-duty steps suitable for extreme terrain, alternative options might be a better fit. Remember, a well-thought-out purchase not only enhances your Jeep but also ensures durability tailored to your driving style.</p>

